# Release Tag On Commit

Whenever this agent creates and pushes a commit to `main`/`master` for this repository:

1. Bump a SemVer patch tag by default (`v0.1.1` → `v0.1.2`), or minor/major when the change clearly warrants it.
2. Create an annotated tag on the new commit.
3. Push the tag with `GIT_SSH_COMMAND="ssh -o Hostname=ssh.github.com -p 443"` when SSH port 22 is blocked.
4. Confirm the `Build & Release` workflow starts for that tag so GitHub Release assets are published.

Do not leave a pushed commit without a corresponding `v*` release tag.
